## рҹ”ә How Auto-Escalation Works

```
Issue created
  в””в”Җ currentLevel : 1  (Ward Admin responsible)
  в””в”Җ priority     : Low
  в””в”Җ status       : Pending

Citizens upvote:
  10+ votes  вҶ’  priority: Medium  (idle timer: 48h Г— 1.0  = 48h)
  25+ votes  вҶ’  priority: High    (idle timer: 48h Г— 0.75 = 36h)
  50+ votes  вҶ’  priority: Critical (idle timer: 48h Г— 0.5 = 24h)

  When a priority threshold is crossed:
  - Priority field updates automatically
  - A system comment is added to the issue
  - lastActivityAt resets (fresh idle timer)

Escalation cron (every 60 min checks all unresolved issues):
  L1 idle > threshold  вҶ’  currentLevel: 2, status: Escalated, assignedTo: cleared
  L2 idle > threshold  вҶ’  currentLevel: 3, status: Escalated, assignedTo: cleared
  L3                   вҶ’  no further escalation вҖ” City Admin must act
```

All thresholds are configurable via environment variables вҖ” no code changes needed.

